events.originalText: Turkish student Özgecan Aslan was murdered during a rape attempt, sparking mass demonstrations across the country after her body was discovered two days later.
events.subtitle: Murder of Özgecan Aslan
events.headline: Turkish student Özgecan Aslan murdered in rape attempt, sparking mass demonstrations

events.originalText: Rebel East Timorese soldiers invaded the homes of President José Ramos-Horta and Prime Minister Xanana Gusmão, seriously wounding the former.
events.subtitle: 2008 East Timorese assassination attempts
events.headline: Rebel East Timorese soldiers invade homes of President José Ramos-Horta and Prime Minister Xanana Gusmão

events.originalText: The computer worm Anna Kournikova, which would affect millions of users worldwide, was released by a 20-year-old Dutch student.
events.subtitle: Computer worm
events.headline: Computer worm Anna Kournikova released by 20-year-old Dutch student, affecting millions worldwide

events.originalText: The Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization was established in The Hague to represent the interests of indigenous peoples, minorities, occupied nations, and other areas lacking international recognition.
events.subtitle: Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization
events.headline: Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization established in The Hague

events.originalText: Anti-apartheid activist Nelson Mandela, having been a political prisoner for 27 years, was released from Victor Verster Prison near Paarl, South Africa.
events.subtitle: Nelson Mandela
events.headline: Anti-apartheid activist Nelson Mandela released from Victor Verster Prison after 27 years

events.originalText: The Frente de Liberación Homosexual made their final public appearance, shortly before the group's dissolution due to political repression after the 1976 Argentine coup d'état.
events.subtitle: Frente de Liberación Homosexual
events.headline: Frente de Liberación Homosexual dissolves after political repression following 1976 Argentine coup d'état

events.originalText: The BBC aired an adaptation of a section of Czech writer Karel Čapek's play R.U.R. in the first broadcast of science fiction on television.
events.subtitle: BBC
events.headline: BBC airs adaptation of Karel Čapek's play R.U.R. in first broadcast of science fiction on television

events.originalText: Friedrich Ebert was elected the provisional president of Germany by the Weimar National Assembly.
events.subtitle: Friedrich Ebert
events.headline: Friedrich Ebert elected provisional president of Germany by Weimar National Assembly

events.originalText: As part of celebrations marking the separation of Victoria from New South Wales, the inaugural first-class cricket match in Australia began at the Launceston Racecourse in Tasmania.
events.subtitle: Victoria (state)
events.headline: Inaugural first-class cricket match in Australia begins at Launceston Racecourse in Tasmania

events.originalText: La fille du régiment (audio featured), an opéra comique by Gaetano Donizetti, premiered in Paris to highly negative reviews but later became a success.
events.subtitle: La fille du régiment
events.headline: La fille du régiment by Gaetano Donizetti premieres in Paris to negative reviews

events.originalText: London University, later University College London (pictured), was founded as the first secular university in England.
events.subtitle: University College London
events.headline: London University, later University College London, founded as first secular university in England

events.originalText: Around 110 boys were killed in a human crush at the Convent of the Minori Osservanti in Valletta on the last day of the Maltese Carnival.
events.subtitle: Carnival tragedy of 1823
events.headline: Around 110 boys killed in human crush at Convent of the Minori Osservanti in Valletta

events.originalText: Spanish explorer Pedro Sarmiento de Gamboa founded the town of Nombre de Jesús, the first of two short-lived colonies at the Strait of Magellan.
events.subtitle: Pedro Sarmiento de Gamboa
events.headline: Spanish explorer Pedro Sarmiento de Gamboa founds town of Nombre de Jesús at the Strait of Magellan
